  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Freedom Collection column lineup we service</h2>
    <p>Thermador Freedom Collection is the US market's most flexible built-in column refrigeration system — the homeowner configures column widths across the kitchen to match the design intent rather than working around a fixed 36\" or 42\" built-in footprint. Column widths: 18\" (freezer or freezer + ice maker), 24\" (refrigerator or freezer), 30\" (refrigerator or freezer), 36\" (refrigerator or freezer or bottom-freezer built-in). Common LA configurations include 36\" refrigerator + 18\" freezer + 18\" wine cooler (54\" kitchen run), 24\" + 24\" + 30\" mixed column (78\" run), or full-Freedom suite with 4-5 columns across a 90+ inch kitchen wall. Each column is a complete independent refrigeration system with its own compressor + temperature control + ice maker (when equipped) + independent service access; service approach isolates to the affected column without disrupting adjacent units.</p>
    <p>Beyond Freedom Collection, Thermador covers traditional built-in formats: <b>T36BB / T36BT / T36IT</b> 36-inch bottom-freezer built-in as single-cabinet alternative to column suite; <b>T36FT</b> 36-inch French-door built-in; legacy Thermador built-in side-by-side platforms from 2010s-era still in active LA service. All current + legacy Thermador built-in platforms service via BSH Irvine parts channel with typical 1-2 day LA-authorized lead on common service components. Panel-ready integrated variants (most Freedom Collection columns available as integrated + stainless stock finish) use full-overlay custom cabinetry panels with BSH-specific panel-attachment hardware.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Common Thermador built-in failures our techs see in LA</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Not cooling — condenser clean + BSH diagnostic</h3><p>Front-mount condenser dust accumulation at 12-24 months reduces airflow → compressor overheats → cooling drops. Deep clean $120–$180 resolves most at no-parts-cost.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>NTC temperature sensor drift — error-code diagnostic</h3><p>BSH error codes specific to sensor location; NTC drift 5-8 year mark. Sensor swap $240–$320; Irvine parts typical 1-2 day lead.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Door gasket compression loss (European spec)</h3><p>European-profile gasket compresses after 10-15 years causing temperature drift + excessive cycling. Per-column $280–$420 replacement.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Evaporator fan motor — single-column airflow dependency</h3><p>Each Freedom Collection column depends entirely on its own evaporator fan; motor failure directly affects that column's cooling. $320–$460 per column motor swap.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Ice maker module (18" freezer + ice variants)</h3><p>Ice maker column failure modes: water inlet valve $260–$360, module $320–$460. T18IF900SP + compatible Freedom variants.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Panel-overlay gasket (integrated models)</h3><p>Integrated Freedom columns use full-overlay panel gasket system. $320–$460 replacement; panel-protection discipline during service.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>BSH Irvine CA parts chain — Thermador LA-local advantage</h2>
    <p>BSH Home Appliances operates a major parts distribution center in Irvine, California that serves Thermador + Bosch + Siemens + Gaggenau OEM components to LA-authorized service dispatch. The Irvine proximity gives Thermador built-in service a meaningful practical advantage: common service components (NTC sensors, water inlet valves, evaporator fan motors, ice maker modules, standard gaskets, start relays) typically ship 1-2 day to LA vs 5-10 day on brands whose parts flow from European or Midwest distribution. Specialty components (full control boards, panel-overlay hardware, legacy-generation OEM) 3-5 day typical via Irvine, occasionally longer when specialty items must route through European manufacturing. For mixed BSH-family kitchens (Thermador refrigerator + Bosch dishwasher + Gaggenau oven, for example), multi-appliance service visits schedule efficiently through shared Irvine parts channel. See also our <a href="/brands/thermador-cooktop-repair/">Thermador cooktop</a>, <a href="/brands/thermador-oven-repair/">oven</a>, <a href="/brands/thermador-dishwasher-repair/">dishwasher</a>, <a href="/brands/thermador-range-hood-repair/">range hood</a>, and <a href="/brands/thermador-ice-maker-repair/">ice maker</a> combos — all serve via the same Irvine chain.</p>
